modules.description: This module offers functions to create, parse, and serialize HTTP cookies, including managing attributes like name, value, path, domain, expiration, and security flags, alongside validation and date-time handling per RFC standards. It operates on structured cookie representations (`t`) and date-time values, enabling precise attribute manipulation, comparison, and error-resilient workflows through result types. Designed for web applications and APIs, it ensures compliant cookie management for session tracking, user authentication, and secure HTTP interactions.
